        "created_at": "2026-02-09T20:08:50.846Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Yes, Molly (they have the option to block unknown contacts!) is there but again this is a third party development and iOS is left out. We are now living in a time where more and more people fall to numerous scams and this is like a cat and mouse game honestly. My few suggestions (and again I want to say sorry if we already have a healthy discussion of such topics, please link it otherwise. memory not that sharp anymore) .</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Text only mode stripping down everything else. Just plain text messages. Signal Lite app?</li>\n<li>Total block of unknown numbers and contacts or usernames. (pls!)</li>\n<li>One click can switch on many other settings such as: disabling link previews, relay calls through signal servers only protecting IP, PIN, registration lock, incognito keyboard, turning off phone number visibility and discoverability, app lock, screen security, payment lock, notification access etc‚Ä¶</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Hope to see some action on these soon‚Ä¶! <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/slight_smile.png?v=15\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
