        "created_at": "2026-02-10T07:49:56.924Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Avitus\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"74660\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/48/34172_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Avitus:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>What would be the purpose of this?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Not being hacked through attachments</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Avitus\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"74660\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/48/34172_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Avitus:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If there is an excessive spam problem to your username, you can change the username to stop it.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Works but if spammers know how Signal internals work, they can still find you even after dropping discoverability and changing the phone number.</p>\n<p>Anyways this should be merged with: <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/lockdown-mode-like-feature-for-signals-mobile-applications/48772\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Lockdown Mode-like feature for Signal's mobile applications</a></p>",
