        "created_at": "2026-02-10T22:51:07.961Z",
        "cooked": "<p>There‚Äôs no real way to fix this in a user friendly way. SimpleX doesn‚Äôt fix this in a way that makes sense to the vast majority of users (I am of the opinion that usernames are <em>good</em> for mass adoption. SimpleX doesn‚Äôt have these in favor of 1 time use links). Spammers will get tired of messaging you through your ACI if you continue to block them.</p>\n<p>I don‚Äôt know what you want Signal to do about this. Blocking all unknown contacts from being able to message you is‚Ä¶ dumb. You cannot foresee all of the cases in which a legitimate person may attempt to contact you.</p>",
